At 11:01 PM 7/20/02, THE SCHMIDTS wrote:
>   1.Is it true that a double cab truck has no 'treasure chest' under the 
> bed?  It appears the rear bench would be in the way, but did any years 
> have a small place to stash stuff?

Not like the SC.  There is space under the rear seat and it extends back a 
little more than a foot beyond the rear window, under the bed.  You should 
see the load of stuff I can store under there.

>2. Is there a double cab-specific roof rack available or do dc owners just 
>adapt standard racks?

I've seen mid sized racks out there, but can't tell you where.

>3. What is the deal with the metal around the DC rear window?  kinda looks 
>like 4 triangle stamps in the metal coming to a point.  Is this finding 
>a  factory marking or some custom crap?

Factory marking.  The stamping adds strength to the metal and keeps the 
rear window from wobbling as you zoom down the road.

>4. Are safari windows any better than they were 10 yrs ago? When the 
>repros came out, everyone complained about them cracking if you drive with 
>them even slightly open.  Are there any good ones available today? When 
>closed, is leaking a problem in the rain?

Look out, here comes the safari FART.  Best check the archives for an 
answer on this one.

>5. Does anyone have a nice 58-61 double cab they would like to sell to a 
